        <item>
            <title>Version 2.3.3</title>
            <description><![CDATA[
                <h2>ForgedBrew 2.3.3</h2>
                <p><strong>Trust Management Screening</strong> (formerly Trust Maintenance) — get ahead of Homebrew's <strong>September 1, 2026</strong> cask quarantine change, when Homebrew stops clearing the macOS quarantine flag for casks.</p>
                <p>This screen now evaluates <strong>every</strong> Homebrew cask app against the four signals macOS Gatekeeper uses to trust an app — code signature, Developer ID, notarization, and Gatekeeper assessment — and flags, app by app, which ones could be blocked after Sept 1 and why. Results split into <em>Trust now</em> (actionable today) and <em>Watch for Sept 1</em> (runs fine now, at risk on a fresh download later). Trust apps one at a time with a deliberate per-app Trust button — no "Trust All."</p>
                <p>Also includes a fix for Sparkle auto-update relaunch when running in the menu bar.</p>
            ]]></description>
            <pubDate>Fri, 19 Jun 2026 15:10:35 +0000</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>233</sparkle:version>
